Paper: hep-th/9507052

Date: 1995-07-08

Title: Symplectic Quantization of the CP$^1$ Model with the Chern-Simons Term

Authors: Yong-Wan Kim, Young-Jai Park, and Yongduk Kim

Comments: 10 pages, latex, no figures, Final published version

Journal-ref: J.Korean Phys.Soc. 28 (1995) 773-776

The symplectic formalism is fully employed to study the gauge-invariantCP$^1$ model with the Chern-Simons term. We consistently accommodate the CP$^1$constraint at the Lagrangian level according to this formalism.